                <head>No. 465<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>According to <persName corresp="#p_HAGERTYJC1">Hagerty</persName>’s diary
                    President <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> and Prime
                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName> had a private
                    conversation for three quarters of an hour in the President’s office shortly
                    after noon on June 25. No record of this conversation has been found in
                    Department of State files. (<persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> Library, <persName corresp="#p_HAGERTYJC1">James C.
                        Hagerty</persName> papers)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
